{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it an offence to use someone's bank card if they're dying in hospital",
        "additional_details": "I'm concerned that someone could take a card while person is in hospital on their deathbed because if they die, they wouldn't be able to report it to the police. The perpetrator can claim they had permission.\r\n \r\nI believe this is a loophole because someone dying from dementia or any other illness in hospital wouldn't be able to give permission as they wouldn't have the capacity to say so.\r\n",
        "background": "Current laws say you can't use someone else's card without their permission but I believe there is a current loophole when someone is dying. ",
